	Notes:	It should be noted that there are various explanations for the name O. One explanation is that O is an anecdotal pseudonym, which refers to the name by which he was called as a child: O, as in Oldest. His Mother, having been self-diagnosed with a medical condition that prevented her from learning anyone\'92s name, found it easier to remember that he was her Oldest son than the fact that he was called John Oliver Grimmer. Perhaps the most obvious explanation is that O is Mr. O\'92s middle name. Another explanation is that it refers to his title, within the Agency, and one of his nickname\'92s amongst the Agents: the Orchestrator (a synonym for Director). Finally, the O may be a reference to the numeral Zero\'85Mr. O is Patient Zero.}